 King Williams Town - During the Festive Season Operations at Zwelitsha King Williams Town Cluster Police members followed up on the information they received about a house that allegedly sells drugs at Dubu Location outside King Williams Town. "Police obtained a search warrant and proceeded to the house and seized 36 quarter Mandrax tablets, 15 half Mandrax tablets, six full boss tablets, 161 Dagga bompies, 15 Tik sachets, nine dagga arms, 75 counterfeit CDs, 13 rizzla papers and an undisclosed amount of cash," said police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa. "The suspect, aged 57, was arrested and charged for dealing with drugs." She said that the suspect is due to appear at Zwelitsha Magistrate's Court soon. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 